{
  "texts": [
    "Such a segmentation method is the work of Meng et al. (2019).",
    "As a basis of the architecture, they used VAE and Radial Basis Function (RBF) (Buhmann 2000) (11), (12).",
    "The authors complain about the ineffectiveness of point clouds due to their unordered nature and lack of symmetry; thus, a voxel grid is proposed.",
    "Typically, a voxel only contains a boolean occupancy status, which is not descriptive enough, but with RBF, they are interpolated, which leads to a representation with more resolution.",
    "where N is the number of data points, w j is the scalar value, (⋅) is the symmetry function, is the center point of a voxel, and v are the data points and:"
  ]
}